{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/spawnchildsetupfunc"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Type Alias","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib19SpawnChildSetupFunca","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SpawnChildSetupFunc","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"typealias","role":"symbol","title":"SpawnChildSetupFunc","fragments":[{"text":"typealias","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SpawnChildSetupFunc","kind":"identifier"}]},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Specifies the type of the setup function passed to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_spawn_async()"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_spawn_sync()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_spawn_async_with_pipes()"},{"type":"text","text":", which can, in very"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"limited ways, be used to affect the child’s execution."}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SpawnChildSetupFunc","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"typealias"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SpawnChildSetupFunc","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" = "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GSpawnChildSetupFunc","text":"GSpawnChildSetupFunc"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"On POSIX platforms, the function is called in the child after GLib","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"has performed all the setup it plans to perform, but before calling","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"exec()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Actions taken in this function will only affect the child,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"not the parent.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On Windows, the function is called in the parent. Its usefulness on"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Windows is thus questionable. In many cases executing the child setup"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"function in the parent can have ill effects, and you should be very"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"careful when porting software to Windows that uses child setup"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"functions."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"However, even on POSIX, you are extremely limited in what you can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"safely do from a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SpawnChildSetupFunc","isActive":true},{"text":", because any mutexes that were","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"held by other threads in the parent process at the time of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fork()"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"will still be locked in the child process, and they will never be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"unlocked (since the threads that held them don’t exist in the child).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"POSIX allows only async-signal-safe functions (see ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"signal(7)"},{"type":"text","text":") to be"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"called in the child between "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fork()"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"exec()"},{"type":"text","text":", which drastically limits"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the usefulness of child setup functions."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In particular, it is not safe to call any function which may"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"call "},{"code":"malloc()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", which includes POSIX functions such as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"setenv()"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"If you need to set up the child environment differently from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the parent, you should use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_get_environ()"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"g_environ_setenv()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_environ_unsetenv()"},{"type":"text","text":", and then pass the complete environment"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"list to the "},{"code":"g_spawn...","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"abstract":[],"kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/glib","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/SpawnChildSetupFunc":{"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"typealias"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"SpawnChildSetupFunc","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/spawnchildsetupfunc","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SpawnChildSetupFunc"}],"title":"SpawnChildSetupFunc","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SpawnChildSetupFunc","abstract":[{"text":"Specifies the type of the setup function passed to ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_spawn_async()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_spawn_sync()"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"g_spawn_async_with_pipes()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", which can, in very"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"limited ways, be used to affect the child’s execution."}]}}}